      The concept of a "Big War" force is a good one which as a strategic concept can be traced back to Mahan's concept of a "Fleet in Being", it is the capability of the U.S. Military to bring overwhealming force to any field that makes conventional state-on-state war much more unlikely simply because such a force allows other nations the opportunity for peaceful resolutions safe in the belief that U.S. national interest in peaceful resolutions would largely preclude agressive moves by any raational state (PAX Americana?). 

                  
